honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl

Class NetworkEthernetSettings_DPL

  • java.lang.Object
    • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.PrinterData_DPL
      • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.PrinterState_DPL
        • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.NetworkEthernetSettings_DPL
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class NetworkEthernetSettings_DPL
extends PrinterState_DPL
    This class handles the network ethernet settings data from the [STX]KcQQQ query as well as accessors to read the data values.

    This class supports the following possible parameters:

    ParameterDescription
    1IP Address Method(DHCP Enable)
    2Static Printer IP Address
    3Static Printer Subnet Mask
    4Static Printer Default Gateway Address
    5PHY Mode
    6PHY Advertise Mode
    7PHY Capability to Advertise
    8MTU
    9Printer TCP Port
    10Default MTU
    11Static Primary WINS Server IP
    12Static Secondary WINS Server IP
    13Static Primary DNS Server IP
    14Static Secondary DNS Server IP
    15SNMP TRAP IP Address
    16SNMP Server IP Address
    17NetBIOS Enable
    18NetBIOS Name
    19Domain Name
    20UDP Port
    21Inactivity Timeout
    22Ethernet MAC Address
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Constructor Detail

      • NetworkEthernetSettings_DPL

        public NetworkEthernetSettings_DPL(ConnectionBase conn)
        The default constructor will initialize the class with default values.

        Initially all of the _IsValid parameters will be false because no data has been processed. To 'populate' the values, the object must invoke @see PrinterState_DPL.queryPrinter(int) with the query response string.

        Parameters:
        conn - connection to printer
